recommend check-in -- the Sala broadcast lane and the SLC flagship are complete (L1 record, L2 live carriage, L3 audience+back-channel), the Pool keystone ladder is closed (P0/P1/R1/R2), and Dexter graduated. This is a substantial milestone and a natural resting point; the branch (P0/P1/B1/R1/R2/B2) is ready whenever Keaton says send. The next work is a genuinely new choice -- harden or package the flagship toward a real device/user (the SLC's own next step), open a fresh lane, or rest -- and deserves Keaton's word rather than an assumed next lap.
